    "description": "<blockquote><p><strong>Requirements:</strong> you must have mastered the <strong>Monk</strong> Class.</p></blockquote><p><span>You learn the ultimate <strong>Monk</strong> spell: <strong>Beaded Weapon</strong>.</span></p><table style=\"width:96.2791%\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width:15.3584%\"></col><col style=\"width:12.9693%\"></col><col style=\"width:27.3038%\"></col><col style=\"width:44.3686%\"></col></colgroup><tbody><tr><td style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Volcano</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>MP:</strong> 40</td><td style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Target:</strong> One equipped weapon</td><td style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Duration:</strong> Scene</td></tr></tbody></table><ul><li><p><span>At any moment, if you have a full set of active Soul Beads, you may imbue one weapon with them. Until this spell ends, the weapon gains a +3 bonus to Accuracy Checks, and its damage ignores Resistances.</span></p></li><li><p><span>If it’s a melee weapon, it also gains the ranged property, and its attacks can now be launched from afar.</span></p></li><li><p><span>If you have that weapon equipped while casting this spell, you may perform a free attack with it as part of the same action.</span></p></li><li><p><span>You lose access to beads used, and they don’t count toward the Clarity Skill while imbued in your weapon.</span></p></li><li><p><span>You can generate Soul Beads as normal on the next turn.</span></p></li><li><p><span>The same weapon cannot benefit from this skill twice.</span></p></li></ul><p>Add the @UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-heroic-skills.Item.xjiGIzpgP523NAV7]{Beaded Weapon} spell to your character sheet.</p>",
